The project has several references to "gaze.‚Äù What does gaze mean in XR?

- In XR, gaze refers to where the player (or user) is looking, which is more complicated than it sounds. 
Usually, gaze tracks with player head or eye movement, and it is governed by field-of-view and headset hardware.
The applications of gaze are wide-ranging, from selecting objects to interacting with NPCs and improving performance
based on where the player is looking with practices such as foveated rendering.
